Snowflake Output Connection

Create a remote connection using the Snowflake output connector to write data from CRM Analytics to a Snowflake table. Then, use Sync Out to push raw data from CRM Analytics to Snowflake, or a Data Prep recipe output node to push transformed data.

How CRM Analytics Output Connectors with Output Nodes Work

CRM Analytics connectors allow you to write the outcome of a recipe to an external system for further analysis, business automation, and storage. 

Generate your Snowflake private key and private key passphrase using the Snowflake Private Key documentation.

Connect to Snowflake with OAuth

Configure Snowflake and your selected external authorization server. Define an Authentication Provider in Salesforce from Configure an Authentication Provider Using OpenID.

Enable and Add the Snowflake Output Connector
From Setup, in the Quick Find box, enter Analytics, select Analytics, and then Settings.
Select Enable Snowflake output connection and then save your changes.
In the Data Manager, click the Connections tab.
Click New Connection.
Click Output.
Click the connector's name to add it.

Connection Name	Identifies the connection
Developer Name	API name for the connection
Description	Description
Authentication Type	The type of authentication used for this connection

The type of authentication used for this connection. Accepted values are "OAuth", "Password", or "PrivateKey".

Named Credential	The Name field from a named credential stored in your Salesforce org.
Username	User name for the Snowflake account.
Password	Optional setting*. Password for your Snowflake account.
Account	Name of your Snowflake account.
Warehouse	Snowflake warehouse name.
Role	Optional setting. Snowflake role assigned to the user that youâ€™re using to connect.
Database	Snowflake database name.
Schema	Snowflake schema name.
Private Key	Optional setting*. A private key associated with your Snowflake account.
Private Key Passphrase	Optional setting*. The passphrase associated with your specified private key.

Push Data to Snowflake

With the Snowflake Output Connector configured, you have two options to push data to Snowflake from CRM Analytics. 

You can use an output connection more than once per recipe, but each output node must use a different object.
